<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF109-495-495  </DOCNO><DOCID>09 495 495.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>The Wall Street Journal  Oct 12 1990 pB5B(W) pB4E(E) 20 col in.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Cable andamp; Wireless unit spearheads plan for Asian regionalfiber-optic network.andO;</TITLE><AUTHOR>Stine, Stephen F.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Hong Kong Telecom International Ltd (HKTI) is one of the leadingparticipants in an effort to improve communications in theAsia-Pacific region with the use of underwater fiber opticnetworks.andP;  HKTI, which is planning to invest $161.3 million, isthe sole supplier of long-distance service in the region and hasenough users to ensure that the investment will pay for itself.andO;The Asian-Pacific region's current telecommunications system hasbeen taxed in recent years and estimates are that it has increased55 percent between 1988 and 1990.andP;  Fiber-optic cabling is a costlyproposition and cooperation has become imperative to install thetelecommunications system.andP;  Fiber-optics offer a cost-effectivealternative to satellite telecommunications since the they surpasssatellites in quality and capacity.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   Hong Kong Telecommunications Ltd. (planning).andO;Topic:     Pacific Rim countriesFiber opticsTelecommunications ServicesInternational Communications.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>